overview: The user aimed to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by adding
  persistent storage for responses and a client-facing dashboard. The approach
  involved updating the application's data models to include detailed
  questionnaire responses and demographic information, then integrating a
  PostgreSQL database using Prisma. A key decision was to implement a simple
  admin dashboard with password-based authentication, allowing the client to
  view and export collected data as CSV. Initially, a custom session management
  system was developed, but it was later streamlined by adopting Next.js
  middleware for more efficient and cleaner route protection. The implementation
  included updating form submissions to save data, creating API endpoints for
  data management, and building the dashboard UI. The database setup was guided
  and verified, ensuring all components worked as expected.
